    "synopsis": "Fulgrim, primarch of the Emperor's Children, is the finest of the Emperor's sons: beautiful, brilliant, devoted to perfection. On the murder-world of Laer, a Legion compliance brings home a daemon-bound sword that has been waiting for him. The blade is patient. The Legion that once aspired to flawless service turns slowly, exquisitely, to excess: composers cut themselves to chase the perfect note, captains take cosmetic mutations as ornament, the seeds of the Noise Marines are sown. Fulgrim carries his treason to bloom at Isstvan V, where the Dropsite Massacre is consummated and he kills his oldest brother, Ferrus Manus of the Iron Hands. By the close he has taken every step the daemon needed him to.",
